cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper proposes a new routing protocol for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) which is a subfield of networking. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses clustering technique in routing protocols which involves data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a dynamic Cluster Head (CH) selection technique which involves multiple agents (sensor nodes) working together. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a fixed number of CHs in each round instead of probabilistic selection which can be seen as a form of supervised learning. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed routing protocol can have implications on the security and privacy of the WSNs.
